WEBVTT

00:28.235 --> 00:31.530
IRMA VEP

02:54.298 --> 02:58.010
Sorry. Am I disturbing you?

03:00.681 --> 03:03.767
I like to spend time on set
before the crew comes

03:03.849 --> 03:06.019
and turns it into chaos.

03:06.603 --> 03:07.938
So do I.

03:09.522 --> 03:11.983
I have to absorb how it
feels as a real place.

03:17.322 --> 03:19.782
I need to make sure it's haunted.

03:21.700 --> 03:26.080
Sorry, I feel safer
if you're not pointing a gun at me.

03:28.415 --> 03:30.084
Am I that dangerous?

03:30.168 --> 03:32.796
You are Irma Vep for me,
so, yes, you are dangerous.

03:33.422 --> 03:36.133
Yeah, but off camera,
I am a nice person.

03:37.216 --> 03:39.927
No, not to me.
Maybe later...

03:40.887 --> 03:42.304
when the shoot is over.

03:43.724 --> 03:48.895
- Is it haunted enough for you?
- The set?

03:50.062 --> 03:55.359
Well, most of the time,
sets are soulless.

03:56.778 --> 04:01.575
- But not this one.
- You have an actual ghost with a gun.

04:02.700 --> 04:07.539
Mira do you believe
in the invisible?

04:08.080 --> 04:13.878
The invisible.
I guess so.

04:14.421 --> 04:16.798
I mean, it depends on
what you call invisible.

04:16.882 --> 04:20.969
Things that exist,
but you cannot see.

04:21.678 --> 04:24.305
- Like what?
- Like...

04:30.687 --> 04:32.229
Wi-Fi.

04:32.688 --> 04:34.816
- Wi-Fi...
- Yeah, Wi-Fi, yeah.

04:35.733 --> 04:42.072
Yeah. But then sometimes

04:42.406 --> 04:44.910
I feel like
it's not there and it's not working.

04:45.368 --> 04:47.370
What about presences?

04:47.829 --> 04:50.873
You mean the way a place
has some sort of soul?

04:50.957 --> 04:52.291
Or not.

04:52.374 --> 04:54.753
That you can't see
but you can feel.

04:55.753 --> 04:57.798
- Yes, yes.
- I do.

04:58.631 --> 05:04.553
Sets are eerie because they're real
and they're not real.

05:05.096 --> 05:08.308
They look real, but they're
an imitation of reality...

05:09.810 --> 05:13.188
just like dreams
are an imitation of reality.

05:14.231 --> 05:15.857
You're right, like dreams.

05:19.444 --> 05:21.863
- Were you rehearsing?
- I was.

05:25.616 --> 05:27.118
Do you want to show me?

05:27.577 --> 05:29.954
Are you sure I should
kill the Grand Vampire?

05:30.037 --> 05:32.082
Oh yes.
We should get rid of him.

05:32.915 --> 05:34.917
He's definitely not
gonna be happy.

05:37.127 --> 05:38.547
Screw him.

05:40.256 --> 05:45.678
I'm here for you,
so I'm in for the ride.

05:46.930 --> 05:50.851
The Grand Vampire visits Moreno
to pay Irma Vep's ransom

06:03.613 --> 06:05.991
"Irma doesn't wish to leave me.
Ask her yourself,"

06:06.073 --> 06:07.659
"she's in the next room."

06:17.751 --> 06:19.212
Still under Moreno's spell,

06:19.295 --> 06:21.423
Irma Vep shoots
to kill the Grand Vampire!

06:26.177 --> 06:28.304
Yes! Great!
Yeah, you did it!

06:28.762 --> 06:32.434
Now shoot him again.
Empty the barrel.

06:34.018 --> 06:35.353
Now, jump on him.

06:35.853 --> 06:39.149
Yeah, with both feet.
Jump on him!

06:39.231 --> 06:42.152
René, I have heels on.
I can't jump on him.

06:42.652 --> 06:46.823
No. He's dead. He doesn't feel nothing.
Jump on him.

06:47.448 --> 06:50.035
- I am so sorry.
- It's okay, it's fine.

06:51.035 --> 06:52.829
You have nothing
to be sorry about.

06:53.955 --> 06:55.539
This is between René and me!

06:55.873 --> 06:57.416
He"s a nutcase!

06:57.499 --> 06:59.419
René, I will sue
the hell out of you!

07:00.128 --> 07:02.713
It's payback time!
You're going down!

07:04.549 --> 07:05.592
Fuck you.

07:06.176 --> 07:08.177
You're dead!
The Grand Vampire is dead!

07:08.678 --> 07:10.680
- Damn right, he's dead!
- Thank you.

07:10.764 --> 07:12.598
He's out of the story! Bye-bye!

07:13.265 --> 07:16.561
I'll see you in arbitration
motherfucker!

07:16.643 --> 07:21.357
Go fuck yourself, scumbag!
Go fuck yourself! Dammit!

07:26.111 --> 07:30.158
I'm done with this Him! Shit!

07:32.702 --> 07:35.621
Get him out of here!

07:35.705 --> 07:40.501
I can't stand him anymore!
I hate Robert! Shit!

07:42.002 --> 07:43.754
Here we go.

07:47.384 --> 07:49.219
- Goodnight.
- Goodnight, Daddy.

07:50.344 --> 07:52.096
- Are they tucked in?
- Yes.

07:57.184 --> 07:59.853
I'm seriously worried.

08:01.814 --> 08:03.649
You are always seriously
worried.

08:04.526 --> 08:08.822
That's part of working with René,
You can't let him do that.

08:09.488 --> 08:11.448
I try. This time, he's gone too far.

08:12.366 --> 08:16.496
He completely lost his shit today,
and Robert is no longer in the show.

08:21.375 --> 08:25.462
- How long have you worked with René?
- 15 years.

08:27.132 --> 08:29.842
Don't you think you need a break?

08:31.927 --> 08:35.140
- I have to protect him.
- From what?

08:35.514 --> 08:40.103
- Himself. He's gone missing.
- Meaning?

08:41.645 --> 08:46.818
I even called his wife. No news.
He's not returning my calls.

08:47.861 --> 08:49.903
I have no idea if we're
shooting tomorrow.

08:50.530 --> 08:52.239
That's an insurance issue.

08:52.322 --> 08:56.618
I'm not sure we're covered
for the director vanishing.

08:58.913 --> 09:00.373
Knock on wood.

09:01.499 --> 09:03.585
That's the
best you can come up with?

09:03.667 --> 09:05.462
Do you want me to sugarcoat it?

09:20.018 --> 09:21.143
Fuck!

09:24.439 --> 09:26.899
- Hello?
- Sorry for disturbing you at this hour.

09:26.982 --> 09:28.984
- We have a small problem.
- Is it René?

09:29.485 --> 09:30.944
No. it's not René.

09:31.028 --> 09:32.863
- What now?
- It's Gottfried.

09:34.156 --> 09:36.618
Jesus! I knew from day one
that he was trouble.

09:36.701 --> 09:38.161
How can I put this?

09:38.243 --> 09:41.622
He hung himself
in some sort of sex game.

09:41.705 --> 09:43.333
What? Is he...

09:43.415 --> 09:47.003
We're not sure
if he's completely alive.

09:47.711 --> 09:49.464
I can't get a straight answer.

09:49.546 --> 09:51.131
- From who?
- The paramedics.

09:51.466 --> 09:52.759
I'm at the hotel now.

09:53.301 --> 09:55.386
I'm going to ask
for their medical report.

09:55.470 --> 09:57.305
Here comes a doctor.
I'll call you back!

09:57.387 --> 10:00.140
Excuse me sir, any news?

10:00.558 --> 10:04.394
He's alive, but he may have
brain damage.

10:04.479 --> 10:08.607
He might make it, but his memory
or mobility may be compromised.

10:09.107 --> 10:13.488
Sorry, can I ask a stupid question?
It's part of my job.

10:14.531 --> 10:19.034
Is there any chance
he can shoot tomorrow?

10:19.577 --> 10:22.037
He'll be lucky if he's alive tomorrow.

10:24.165 --> 10:25.415
Okay...

10:25.499 --> 10:30.255
Excuse us. Coming through, thanks.
I'D ride with the patient.

10:30.337 --> 10:34.800
They're waiting for us there.

10:35.260 --> 10:39.471
Perfect. Ready, lift. I'm lifting.

10:46.228 --> 10:49.065
Hello?
They finally left for the hospital.

10:49.147 --> 10:51.943
I'm jumping on my scooter
to follow them.

10:52.694 --> 10:55.904
I can't tell you more than
what the doctor just said.

10:55.989 --> 10:59.450
- Gautier's calling.
- You called him?

10:59.533 --> 11:03.453
- Of course. I had to.
- I don't envy you. Good luck.

11:03.996 --> 11:05.956
Call me as soon
as they've scanned him.

11:06.039 --> 11:07.709
I'll keep you posted.

11:09.960 --> 11:13.590
- Thanks for calling back.
- Just got your message.

11:13.923 --> 11:17.384
- You sounded very concerned.
- Yes. We have kind of an issue.

11:17.844 --> 11:19.179
Concerning Mira?

11:19.262 --> 11:24.558
No. The problem is
with the German actor. Gottfried.

11:25.225 --> 11:27.604
Gottfried?
I frankly don't remember him.

11:27.686 --> 11:29.771
You scared me for a moment.

11:31.481 --> 11:34.152
What's goina on
with this German actor?

11:35.235 --> 11:39.281
It's a sensitive situation.
He's been hospitalized.

11:39.782 --> 11:43.828
- Poor guy. An accident?
- Yes, sort of...

11:43.912 --> 11:45.162
Did it happen on set?

11:45.246 --> 11:48.290
No, in his hotel room.
He was found in the closet.

11:48.707 --> 11:50.626
What do you mean?

11:51.085 --> 11:54.421
As you may know,
when a man is hanged...

11:54.756 --> 12:00.887
he has a spontaneous,
automatic erection.

12:03.513 --> 12:06.226
Well no, I didn't know that.

12:06.308 --> 12:10.104
Some people use a noose
or a belt to hang themselves

12:10.187 --> 12:15.485
from a closet rod for the purpose
of sexual arousal.

12:16.277 --> 12:18.278
"Autoerotic asohvxiation."

12:18.363 --> 12:21.657
"Autoerotic asphyxiation?"
He sounds insane...

12:22.116 --> 12:24.242
Why wasn't he kept
on a tighter leash?

12:24.577 --> 12:26.829
He had a PA who was
attached to him at the hip.

12:27.245 --> 12:30.959
But apparently Gottfried insisted
on going to a "bear bar,"

12:31.876 --> 12:35.629
which is the kind of place you
go to cruise older, heavy, gay men.

12:36.714 --> 12:40.550
I've never been
to a place like that.

12:40.635 --> 12:43.679
But it seems people like it.

12:44.179 --> 12:45.807
When did this happen?

12:45.889 --> 12:48.392
We dont know. He wasn't
answering his phone.

12:48.476 --> 12:52.145
Carta had the door busted open,
and they found him in the closet.

12:52.230 --> 12:55.273
- Alive?
- Technically speaking, yes.

12:55.358 --> 12:59.820
- But unconscious.
- Are you saying he's braindead?

13:00.196 --> 13:02.156
No, but the prognosis is not good.

13:03.449 --> 13:07.953
Get in touch with our lawyer.
I'll email you his contact info.

13:08.913 --> 13:11.624
- I'll do it first thing in the morning.
- No, right now.

13:12.542 --> 13:15.252
- Very good.
- Not a word to anyone.

13:15.335 --> 13:19.340
You'll let him handle communication
with his agent, family, etc...

13:20.758 --> 13:25.305
We're doing damage control now.
What are his chances of survival?

13:26.179 --> 13:27.390
Poor.

13:29.350 --> 13:32.561
It's a very unusual case.
But we do see them once in a while.

13:32.645 --> 13:36.064
Usually on weekends.
Saturday nights.

13:36.149 --> 13:39.609
You know... the family
is away, they get bored.

13:40.028 --> 13:44.281
How pathetic. What are
Gottfried's odds, 50/50?

13:45.449 --> 13:48.786
Sometimes they come back,
sometimes they dont.

13:50.121 --> 13:54.458
- In this case, I'd say 30/70.
- 30/70?

13:54.542 --> 13:56.461
Maybe 25/75...

13:57.795 --> 14:01.549
Have you reached René?
Keep trying him.

14:02.759 --> 14:05.887
I'm coming to the production office.
We cant shoot today.

14:07.763 --> 14:13.351
Do not call Mirai Gautier's lawyers
are contacting her agent.

14:14.561 --> 14:17.440
I'm iust oraving he'll resurface
before Gautier ever finds out.

14:18.775 --> 14:21.151
Angus, obviously we're not
shooting today,

14:21.235 --> 14:23.904
but we know we can switch
these 2 weeks on our schedule,

14:23.988 --> 14:25.739
and start shooting on Saturdays.

14:25.823 --> 14:28.325
On Fridays, Edmond Lagrange
is doing a play.

14:28.409 --> 14:32.872
He's playing Les Fourberies
de Scapinin St. Etienne.

14:33.915 --> 14:36.541
It's great for him.
Will the crew work on Saturdays?

14:36.626 --> 14:38.001
We'll figure something out.

14:38.086 --> 14:40.171
- A cofffee?
- Thank vou.

14:43.174 --> 14:46.677
When were you going
to tell me that René's gone?

14:46.761 --> 14:50.138
This just happened yesterday
after the blow up with Robert.

14:50.222 --> 14:53.684
- He left set and didn't come back.
- Called him. Nothing new.

14:56.269 --> 14:58.563
We have to consider replacing him.

14:59.982 --> 15:02.568
Does he even know
Gottfried attempted suicide?

15:02.651 --> 15:04.444
Technically, it wasn't suicide.

15:04.529 --> 15:06.864
It was more like a...
sex game.

15:06.947 --> 15:09.950
Let's not speak about the sex game
because it's not sure.

15:10.033 --> 15:13.829
We don't know.
The doctor has to let us know still.

15:13.913 --> 15:17.041
Let's give him a bit more time.
I think he's going to resurface.

15:17.457 --> 15:20.920
- Let's call his agent.
- His agent isn't helpful.

15:23.588 --> 15:26.300
To hide this... What a mess!

15:28.136 --> 15:31.639
- Hi Angus, you good?
- To be honest, no.

15:32.014 --> 15:34.267
Gautier will be furious
to hear about René.

15:34.350 --> 15:36.602
- I hear you.
- You're on speaker.

15:36.686 --> 15:38.603
- Hello.
- Hello, Vladimir.

15:38.688 --> 15:42.357
- Have you heard from him?
- No. I made the rounds. Nothing yet.

15:42.442 --> 15:43.817
What should we do?

15:45.069 --> 15:47.947
Be patient.
It's been less than 24 hours.

15:48.030 --> 15:50.783
We've already been very patient
with your client.

15:50.866 --> 15:53.827
You can't shoot
with an actor in the ICU.

15:53.911 --> 15:58.207
We can shuffle the schedule.
You know how it works.

15:58.915 --> 16:01.918
Gautier's so sick of René's bullshit.

16:02.335 --> 16:05.673
René doesn't matter...

16:05.756 --> 16:08.174
I'm sorry but he fired Robert Danjou,

16:08.259 --> 16:12.430
a man who is a fine actor and
gentleman.

16:12.512 --> 16:15.473
He's humiliated him.
We may have a lawsuit on ourhands l

16:16.225 --> 16:19.144
That's filmmaking. Shit happens!

16:19.854 --> 16:21.897
No, this is chaos.
This is the last straw.

16:21.980 --> 16:23.690
We won't tolerate it anymore.

16:23.774 --> 16:25.735
Who knows, René may have had an
accident.

16:26.402 --> 16:29.780
We're getting nowhere. If he doesn't
surface by soon, he's fired.

16:29.864 --> 16:32.324
- If he calls you, tell him that.
- Got it.

16:32.407 --> 16:35.535
- See ya.
- Bye.

16:35.620 --> 16:38.830
- He's useless.
- That's an understatement!

16:38.915 --> 16:40.958
Luckily, I've been working on plan B.

16:41.041 --> 16:42.126
What's plan B?

16:42.208 --> 16:44.294
I was in touch
with Herman Ray's agent.

16:44.754 --> 16:47.381
Herman? the Herman from
Doomsday?

16:47.465 --> 16:50.175
It'll iust require a little finessing.

16:50.258 --> 16:53.053
I'm really not sure Herman
is the right fit.

16:53.763 --> 16:56.806
This show is very European,
it's not his style.

16:57.182 --> 17:01.145
It's his experience,
people know this...

17:01.687 --> 17:03.940
Doomsday has nothing to do
with The Vampires.

17:04.941 --> 17:06.566
They're polar opposites.

17:06.651 --> 17:09.986
- No? Is it just me?
- I've already zoomed with his people.

17:10.321 --> 17:12.155
They'd seriouslv consider an offer.

18:35.323 --> 18:37.032
Stop!

18:58.470 --> 19:02.307
- My god.
- Hi. Are you okay?

19:03.099 --> 19:05.727
- Yeah. I"m totally fine.
- You sure?

19:05.811 --> 19:07.020
How good to see you.

19:08.396 --> 19:10.358
Yes. In the hotel.

19:10.440 --> 19:14.027
I was, coming out of the elevator
and I saw him right there.

19:14.652 --> 19:16.072
And he passed out.

19:16.738 --> 19:18.740
No, he's fine.
He's in the shower.

19:18.823 --> 19:21.452
I put him in a cold shower.
I think he"s fine right now.

19:21.868 --> 19:23.871
He didn't seem any
less coherent than usual.

19:23.953 --> 19:25.998
He just wanted
to go straight to set.

19:26.081 --> 19:28.124
And I was like,
"No, you need to rest."

19:29.085 --> 19:30.836
Yeah. No, it's fine.

19:31.544 --> 19:34.006
I think he's done with the shower.
I"ll call you back?

19:36.299 --> 19:37.927
What the fuck happened to you?

19:38.635 --> 19:40.095
I don't know.

19:40.178 --> 19:42.098
I was quietly sitting
in my hotel room

19:43.223 --> 19:46.268
reading this really cool book
about drugs in Nazi Germany.

19:46.351 --> 19:48.186
"Blitzed."
Heard of it?

19:48.770 --> 19:50.481
- Never.
- It's fascinating.

19:50.563 --> 19:53.109
Did you know all those
elite troops were on speed?

19:54.402 --> 19:57.446
- Okay.
- Then there was a blank.

19:58.322 --> 20:01.158
I woke up in a clinic...
drips in my arms.

20:02.075 --> 20:03.744
Well, let me fill you in.

20:04.077 --> 20:07.164
Seems you hung yourself
in the closet and passed out.

20:07.789 --> 20:11.167
Now I understand the neck pain
and the strangulation...

20:11.252 --> 20:13.129
- I guess so.
- Strangulation mark.

20:13.211 --> 20:15.172
- I was wondering.
- Please, eat something.

20:15.756 --> 20:17.423
Yeah, nothing to worry about.

20:17.508 --> 20:19.635
Something I do if
I can"t get my dick up.

20:20.970 --> 20:22.304
Does it work?

20:22.387 --> 20:24.598
Usually, it works,
but sometimes I black out.

20:24.681 --> 20:27.935
- It's a thin line.
- Seems this one was close.

20:29.144 --> 20:31.355
- I've done much worse.
- I"m sure.

20:32.732 --> 20:36.693
But now I feel fit as fuck.
It just boosts you.

20:38.612 --> 20:40.239
You have no idea.

20:40.321 --> 20:42.825
Seems the brain scan
showed no lesion, so...

20:50.790 --> 20:52.625
Yeah, I think it's
an excellent offer.

20:52.710 --> 20:54.545
I need to discuss it
again with Laurie.

21:02.552 --> 21:05.765
Me and my team, we had
a second Zoom with the French.

21:07.515 --> 21:09.851
And they seriously want
me to finish "Irma Vep."

21:10.351 --> 21:12.395
- You're really considering it?
- Yeah.

21:13.147 --> 21:15.565
I mean, I ain't give 'em
my decision yet.

21:15.649 --> 21:17.193
I told 'em to wait
till tomorrow.

21:17.276 --> 21:19.444
But Marvel pushed
back "Sharkman," and...

21:20.195 --> 21:22.531
thought you"d be happy to go
to Paris for a few weeks.

21:22.614 --> 21:24.407
- I am.
- And the money's good.

21:24.908 --> 21:27.453
I'm sorry to be blunt,
but it"s basically a hack job.

21:27.995 --> 21:30.289
What you talkin' 'bout?
I mean, it"s a prestige gig.

21:30.371 --> 21:32.625
Honey, you shouldn't be
doing a TV show right now.

21:32.958 --> 21:34.752
- It's bad for your image.
- How?

21:34.834 --> 21:39.089
"Doomsday" performed well,
so you can build on the momentum.

21:40.174 --> 21:42.467
This "Irma Vep" thing's
gonna take you nowhere.

21:42.551 --> 21:44.010
So you don't wanna go to Paris?

21:44.094 --> 21:47.096
Of course, I wanna go to Paris.
Who doesn't wanna go to Paris?

21:48.265 --> 21:49.724
But I care about you.

21:50.309 --> 21:52.478
I'm concerned about
you and Mira, though.

21:53.813 --> 21:55.939
- No reason to be.
- I sense there's no closure.

21:56.522 --> 21:58.484
I don"t know about her, but...

21:59.485 --> 22:01.903
I'm perfectly fine with being
just friends with her.

22:03.988 --> 22:05.823
At a distance... of course.

22:05.907 --> 22:08.451
If we do go, we'll make sure
there's distance.

22:08.534 --> 22:11.163
Thank you. What the fuck happened
with René Vidal?

22:11.247 --> 22:13.164
Apparently,
that motherfucker vanished.

22:13.249 --> 22:15.084
- Really?
- Yeah. Cut his phone off.

22:15.167 --> 22:17.169
- Nobody can contact him.
- You tried?

22:17.253 --> 22:19.379
- I sent him a text.
- Did he text you back?

22:20.089 --> 22:23.132
Kinda.
He never seen no GIF like this.

22:24.676 --> 22:27.638
See, I interpret it
as him sayin', "Be my guest."

22:29.555 --> 22:34.269
