less nuanced, like, "Go fuck yourself."

22:37.565 --> 22:40.316
Have you tried René again?
Turned his cell off.

22:41.859 --> 22:44.404
I sent him a couple texts.
I"m not surprised.

22:46.281 --> 22:47.824
Just disappointed.

22:47.908 --> 22:49.867
I committed to this show
because of René.

22:52.036 --> 22:53.497
I could feel betrayed.

22:53.579 --> 22:55.665
- I'm sure he's in pain.
- I know.

22:55.749 --> 22:57.376
But now we're stuck with Herman.

22:57.709 --> 22:59.085
They need your approval.

22:59.169 --> 23:01.005
You know I'm going
to give my approval.

23:01.505 --> 23:03.798
There aren't many
options anyway.

23:05.008 --> 23:07.969
- At least he"s the evil I know.
- Herman is not evil.

23:11.640 --> 23:13.767
- I'm scared though.
- Why?

23:15.102 --> 23:17.688
- I miss Laurie.
- I don't.

23:19.397 --> 23:20.898
I called her this morning.

23:20.982 --> 23:23.402
- She didn't pick up.
- Why the fuck did you call her?

23:23.818 --> 23:25.195
She'll be in town.

23:26.530 --> 23:28.157
We might as well set the rules.

23:28.990 --> 23:30.533
Laurie doesn't play by any rule.

23:32.118 --> 23:34.371
Don't let her hurt you
more than she already has.

23:43.421 --> 23:44.630
- Hello.
- Come in.

23:55.267 --> 23:56.518
So?

23:57.353 --> 23:59.520
I haven't been
home since yesterday morning.

24:00.481 --> 24:03.900
- I wandered through Paris all night.
- Have vou contacted your wife?

24:03.983 --> 24:05.234
No, no, actually...

24:05.318 --> 24:09.947
When I'm shooting, my wife goes
out of town. She takes the kids.

24:10.032 --> 24:12.201
They usually
stay with her mother.

24:13.410 --> 24:17.830
According to her,
I'm unbearable when I shoot.

24:18.958 --> 24:20.042
Are you?

24:20.124 --> 24:26.923
I cant say I disagree with her.
I made a terrible mistake.

24:28.050 --> 24:33.471
I shouldn't be doing this series.
I'm going to back out.

24:34.390 --> 24:36.766
I thought you carefully thought
this through?

24:36.849 --> 24:39.894
- Not thoroughly enough.
- It could be therapeutic.

24:40.770 --> 24:43.983
- It hasn't been.
- Why do you say that?

24:44.607 --> 24:51.406
A few days ago I received
a visit from Jade's ghost.

24:51.991 --> 24:53.533
- Her ghost?
- Yes.

24:53.617 --> 24:57.246
- Is she dead?
- No. She's alive. But she was there.

24:58.121 --> 25:03.794
Excuse me. Yes?

25:04.336 --> 25:06.922
Could you put the envelope
under the doormat?

25:07.547 --> 25:10.509
Thanks. Sorry.

25:13.721 --> 25:16.056
So, ten years later,
she's still haunting you.

25:16.139 --> 25:19.184
- Twelve years!
- Sorry. Twelve.

25:19.727 --> 25:24.772
I believed that making this long,
eight-hour film,

25:24.857 --> 25:27.650
would bring some sort of closure.

25:28.485 --> 25:32.864
But I haven't found closure.
I'm just opening up old wounds.

25:33.198 --> 25:36.242
You've said Mira embodies
the possibility of a new beginning.

25:36.326 --> 25:38.077
That's true. Yes.

25:40.413 --> 25:45.918
- Do you love her?
- Yes. I love her. Of course I do.

25:46.003 --> 25:50.924
She's a kindred spirit.
But it's something else.

25:51.258 --> 25:53.343
No less valuable than
what I had with Jade.

25:53.844 --> 25:58.431
- And she's not a ghost.
- No. She's so alive, so full of life.

25:59.390 --> 26:05.897
But you know ghosts have very little to
do with the dead.

26:06.899 --> 26:11.694
They're more
about what's dead inside us.

26:13.655 --> 26:17.576
More about the
past that lives inside us.

26:19.912 --> 26:23.998
All that is foreian to Mira.
She's the cure.

26:24.749 --> 26:26.542
- She cures you?
- Yes.

26:26.627 --> 26:32.216
But I also want to protect her
from my disease.

26:34.133 --> 26:36.719
- Your disease?
- Yes, yester...

26:38.554 --> 26:39.723
Sorry.

26:41.225 --> 26:47.146
I had a happening yesterday.

26:48.147 --> 26:50.066
- What happened?
- It was that actor.

26:51.526 --> 26:54.113
I wish I'd killed him.

26:55.030 --> 26:57.823
You've struggled
with these homicidal impulses,

26:57.908 --> 26:59.450
mostly when you're on set.

26:59.535 --> 27:02.495
You've made great progress
over the past few years.

27:02.828 --> 27:07.835
They came back. With a vengeance,
after being kept at bay.

27:08.292 --> 27:12.798
Why do you think you couldn't
control your anger yesterday?

27:13.756 --> 27:16.133
- Is there a reason?
- Yes...

27:17.511 --> 27:19.346
Can you share it?

27:19.428 --> 27:24.226
That actor took umbrage
with an abduction scene,

27:24.309 --> 27:28.104
one that is iconic in
Feuillade's original show.

27:29.565 --> 27:34.653
And he called
this abduction scene a rape.

27:35.069 --> 27:38.907
Abduction means taking someone
against their will.

27:38.990 --> 27:42.118
In that sense, there's a link to rape.

27:42.201 --> 27:44.580
Are you saying the actor was right?

27:45.580 --> 27:49.293
I'm not calling you a rapist.
I think you're anything but...

27:49.917 --> 27:51.628
I'm iust explaining the mechanics.

27:52.129 --> 27:53.255
I hate him.

27:53.337 --> 27:56.300
He's blocking you from doing
what you desire.

27:56.383 --> 27:58.509
- My desire?
- Your cinematic fantasies.

28:21.867 --> 28:25.871
Remind me who this Herman person we
just hired is?

28:25.953 --> 28:28.539
A big director. He just did Doomsday
with Mira.

28:28.624 --> 28:31.709
Right, that film where
Ragnar gets his balls cut off!

28:31.793 --> 28:33.002
That's the one.

28:35.338 --> 28:39.676
My wife told me she liked K a lot.
But they're killing the franchise.

28:39.759 --> 28:42.053
How can there be another Doomsday
without Ragnar?

28:42.136 --> 28:45.682
No, is a smart move.
Ragnar comes back as transgender.

28:46.099 --> 28:48.934
The first trans superhero.
A visionary proiect.

28:49.435 --> 28:51.855
What does Mira think about Herman?

28:52.356 --> 28:55.025
To be honest she wasn't too thrilled.
But what can we do?

28:55.107 --> 28:56.692
René's missing. She understands.

28:56.777 --> 28:58.904
They did Doomsday together.
They're close.

28:59.278 --> 29:04.451
This is all good news. Have you
discussed Herman with the insurers?

29:04.533 --> 29:08.120
The insurers are willing to help as long
as we vacate the lot as planned.

29:08.204 --> 29:09.539
Too expensive to keep it.

29:09.623 --> 29:13.043
That'll be impossible. Herman doesn't
land until Monday morning.

29:13.125 --> 29:16.253
He'll drop his bags at the Plaza Athénée,
do some location scouting.

29:16.338 --> 29:17.965
He'll be ready to shoot on Tuesday.

29:18.047 --> 29:21.843
The insurers need us to shoot tomorrow,
dismantle the set, and vacate the lot.

29:21.926 --> 29:23.260
So, we need a director.

29:23.637 --> 29:27.849
When I spoke to Mira, she suggested
her assistant, Regina, could direct.

29:27.932 --> 29:29.643
She insists she can do it.

29:30.477 --> 29:32.854
- Good.
- Regina is straight out of filmschool.

29:32.937 --> 29:34.940
I've seen her shorts.
She's talented.

29:35.856 --> 29:40.112
We could do worse than her.
She's developing a feature.

29:40.778 --> 29:42.447
I might even
be interested in buying it.

29:42.530 --> 29:46.660
Give the kid a break, make Mira happy.
Then Herbert takes over.

29:47.034 --> 29:48.536
- Herman!
- What?

29:48.619 --> 29:51.248
- His name is Herman.
. Herman!

29:53.375 --> 29:54.875
I'm in a complete panic.

29:55.334 --> 29:58.003
They want me to replace
René just to save the day.

29:58.880 --> 30:01.549
Sounds like a great
opportunity to me. Grab it.

30:02.718 --> 30:05.469
But I'm not prepared,
and it's not even my project.

30:05.929 --> 30:08.347
- Make it your project.
- For a day?

30:08.724 --> 30:10.182
Mira needs your help.

30:10.266 --> 30:12.644
I'm the one who needs
all the help I can get.

30:12.728 --> 30:15.564
Oh, come on. You'll be fine.
It's only one scene.

30:19.567 --> 30:21.028
Let me show you something.

30:21.986 --> 30:24.530
I stayed up all night
looking up references to prep.

30:27.992 --> 30:30.620
- What the hell is that?
- You know Kenneth Anger?

30:31.455 --> 30:32.913
Experimental filmmaker.

30:33.332 --> 30:35.541
René always mentions
him as an inspiration.

30:37.376 --> 30:38.919
Should I know him?

30:39.004 --> 30:41.923
He doesn't see himself
as a director, but as a magus.

30:42.716 --> 30:45.761
- You mean a magician?
- No, magicians do tricks.

30:46.845 --> 30:50.182
A magus believes in...
invisible forces.

30:51.182 --> 30:53.143
He believes that
actors are spirits

30:53.225 --> 30:55.060
and movies are magic rituals.

30:55.645 --> 30:59.316
And what exactly is the purpose
of movies as magic rituals?

30:59.858 --> 31:01.485
To invoke Lucifer.

31:21.046 --> 31:24.298
You mean some sort
of satanic ceremony?

31:24.383 --> 31:26.091
No, not at all.

31:26.176 --> 31:28.135
It's like Lucifer
is the fallen angel

31:29.638 --> 31:31.431
but he's literally
the carrier of light.

31:31.764 --> 31:34.391
His movies are about
conjuring Lucifer?

31:34.725 --> 31:36.937
No, they're about
accessing that light.

31:37.770 --> 31:39.189
What's your point?

31:39.981 --> 31:42.191
All movies are about
accessing the light.

31:42.274 --> 31:43.860
All movies are about...

31:46.195 --> 31:48.239
- Maybe the good ones.
- Yeah, the good ones.

31:49.740 --> 31:51.701
And if you don"t believe
in the invisible,

31:51.785 --> 31:53.787
then you just don"t
make good movies.

31:53.870 --> 31:56.247
Is this something that they
taught you in film school?

31:56.330 --> 31:59.042
No, and this is the part of cinema
you gotta learn by yourself.

31:59.708 --> 32:01.252
No one teaches you that.

32:01.336 --> 32:03.128
You know you sound
exactly like René?

32:04.464 --> 32:07.007
- Your blouse.
- Thank you, Ms. Director.

32:07.676 --> 32:09.177
Only for the day.

32:09.261 --> 32:11.555
And then I'll turn back
into my usual pumpkin.

32:13.514 --> 32:16.518
Look, here's Anaiis Nin
as Astarte.

32:16.600 --> 32:19.146
- Goddess of the Moon.
- She plays Astarte?

32:19.562 --> 32:22.940
No. I mean, she's...
being Astarte.

32:23.608 --> 32:25.484
You know, that"s
the major difference.

32:25.569 --> 32:28.029
So, you mean that
I have to be Irma Vep?

32:28.989 --> 32:31.991
No, you have to let
Irma Vep be you.

32:32.074 --> 32:34.118
For "The Vampires"
to be a better show?

32:34.202 --> 32:35.661
For "The Vampires" to be art.

32:36.662 --> 32:38.415
- As opposed to?
- Entertainment.

32:39.416 --> 32:41.293
It's not supposed
to be entertaining?

32:41.375 --> 32:43.587
Well, of course, it's supposed
to be entertaining,

32:43.670 --> 32:45.087
but it could be more than that.

32:45.838 --> 32:48.258
So, how do you
see your first shot?

32:53.387 --> 32:57.225
First, the camera's here...
the entrance to Moreno"s flat.

32:58.350 --> 33:02.606
And then, we have a close-up
of the nefarious Satanas

33:03.814 --> 33:06.568
as he puts on his
poisonous spike.

33:08.403 --> 33:09.946
Then he rings Moreno's bell

33:10.697 --> 33:14.326
to confront him and Irma Vep about
the Grand Vampire's murder.

33:18.704 --> 33:20.789
Moreno and Irma Vep
had just finished hiding

33:20.874 --> 33:22.625
the Grand Vampire's body
in a chest.

33:39.100 --> 33:40.851
"Not the paralyptic spike!"

33:41.478 --> 33:42.729
And action.

33:53.822 --> 33:56.533
Don't worry, my dear.
He's only paralyzed.

33:58.495 --> 34:00.412
In five minutes,
he'll be back to normal.

34:02.040 --> 34:03.999
And he will have
learned his lesson.

34:04.083 --> 34:06.418
No one messes with The Vampires.

34:08.170 --> 34:10.089
The man you killed
and whose body...

34:11.508 --> 34:14.218
is in this trunk,
was a subordinate.

34:15.053 --> 34:19.307
I, Satanas...
am the true Grand Vampire.

34:22.936 --> 34:24.729
I want you to join The Vampires.

34:26.815 --> 34:29.401
If you don't swear your allegiance
to me by tomorrow,

34:30.317 --> 34:32.236
you will be killed at 2 AM.

34:35.114 --> 34:37.116
The next night,
Moreno and Irma Vep dine

34:37.199 --> 34:38.951
at a cabaret in Montmartre.

34:57.846 --> 35:00.265
You have declinde my generous
offer to join the Vampires

35:00.347 --> 35:02.474
at 2 a.m., you will die.
Satans the Grand Vampire

35:09.189 --> 35:11.901
And now, we bring you
an excerpt from Musidora's memoir...

35:13.944 --> 35:17.157
The morning we shot
the memorable cabaret scene,

35:17.823 --> 35:21.201
I received a telegram from Director
Feuillade which read:

35:22.162 --> 35:27.334
"Please report to the Gaumont studio,
for the shoot of a hazardous scene"

35:28.709 --> 35:32.713
"Bring an elegant but used gown,
for it might be damaged."

35:32.797 --> 35:35.049
"I put it all in a box,"

35:36.133 --> 35:41.847
"and headed" to the nearby
metro station, Botzaris,"

35:42.264 --> 35:44.016
"with my
precious dress in hand."

35:44.391 --> 35:46.977
Yesterday you said it wasn't dear,
so I drew it out for you.

35:48.187 --> 35:50.065
- What's this?
- That's our scene.

35:50.147 --> 35:51.231
Continue.

35:52.691 --> 35:56.071
My partner Femand Herrmann,
who played Moreno,

35:56.570 --> 35:58.907
was waiting
for me on the cabaret set.

35:59.990 --> 36:01.451
Madam Musidora...

36:02.869 --> 36:05.829
This is the cabaret, where I'm treating
you to dinner.

36:06.413 --> 36:10.710
Gaumont Productions
is footing the bill.

36:12.503 --> 36:17.841
The champagne is flowing.
Have a taste. Enioy.

36:23.680 --> 36:30.105
- Warm beer. Could be worse.
- No ice in the bucket...

36:30.605 --> 36:34.150
D'accord, d'accord.

36:36.610 --> 36:41.281
This is the message from Satanas.
He will strike at 2 a.m. 2 a.m!

36:50.291 --> 36:52.835
Excuse me.
What are you supposed to be?

36:53.752 --> 36:56.880
- A tango dancer. Shit!
- Sit. You'll dine instead.

36:59.217 --> 37:01.970
Come with me. You're not dining.

37:02.052 --> 37:05.222
You're wearing a tuxedo with a white tie,
which makes no sense.

37:05.305 --> 37:07.474
- You'll be a waiter.
- Oui.

37:07.559 --> 37:09.893
Have wardrobe put
a towel on your arm.

37:09.977 --> 37:11.187
Ok.

37:11.271 --> 37:14.899
I'll set the scene. You're socialites,
in high spirits.

37:14.983 --> 37:19.112
When the dancers enter, I want
everyone looking at them.

37:20.487 --> 37:24.701
Silence, please! Irma Vep
and her lover Moreno have just

37:24.784 --> 37:29.705
received word that Satanas is still
planning to kill them here at 2 a.m.

37:30.457 --> 37:35.837
And listen up, everyone. There are
two categories of extras today.

37:36.713 --> 37:39.966
The regular extras will earn
the usual daily rate.

37:40.049 --> 37:45.680
Those directly affected by the
blast will get double the rate.

37:46.306 --> 37:51.602
If you're interested in double pay,
step now to your left.

37:53.228 --> 38:00.153
All others to your right.
Double pay is that way.

38:02.280 --> 38:06.576
For safety, go behind that shield
while you're shooting.

38:06.951 --> 38:08.495
I'm gonna get behind the shield.

38:09.120 --> 38:10.370
- Mr. Feuillade!
- Yes?

38:10.454 --> 38:11.955
- Sorry to interrupt.
- Yes.

38:12.707 --> 38:15.125
I think you're going to be very happy
with my explosive.

38:15.751 --> 38:18.087
A renowned pyrotechnician
gave me the formula.

38:18.837 --> 38:21.965
However, I'm afraid some extras
may get injured.

38:23.008 --> 38:26.846
Injuries are fine.
We're ready to shoot.

38:28.222 --> 38:30.849
Meanwhile, at Satana's hideout
across the street...

38:51.246 --> 38:53.540
"Open the window, so I can aim
at the cabaret."

38:55.667 --> 38:57.502
Extras, we're shooting!

38:59.170 --> 39:00.420
Dance!

39:02.005 --> 39:07.053
Very good. Enter, waiter.

39:07.595 --> 39:11.848
Serve the glass of champagne.
Then pour some wine

39:11.932 --> 39:14.643
for the lone customer
at the next table.

39:18.064 --> 39:20.483
Then serve Moreno and Musidora.

39:20.899 --> 39:22.068
Waiter.

39:24.069 --> 39:25.280
Champagne.

39:25.363 --> 39:28.408
Serve them!

39:31.743 --> 39:33.037
Musidora toasts...

39:33.121 --> 39:34.371
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

39:34.706 --> 39:36.082
And drinks.

39:42.087 --> 39:44.214
Here comes the signal.

39:59.396 --> 40:02.482
The set collapsed on top of us.

40:04.277 --> 40:05.736
We thought we were dead.

40:06.446 --> 40:10.199
I can't hear a thing!
I've gone deaf!

40:11.450 --> 40:14.287
It's the end of my career!

40:18.499 --> 40:21.544
For a bomb, that was some bomb!

40:22.377 --> 40:24.838
Triple pay for all the wounded!

40:30.719 --> 40:35.891
Don't, don't leave any messages.

40:36.267 --> 40:38.227
I will never return them.
Thank you.

40:46.401 --> 40:48.696
Have you arrived?
Want have a drink?

40:48.780 --> 40:50.239
Can I see u?

43:48.917 --> 43:51.336
We could redo the buttons.
We could send it to Mike.

43:51.419 --> 43:52.963
He did all the buttons
for "Doomsday."

43:53.046 --> 43:54.257
He'll do it, you think?

43:54.340 --> 43:56.675
Yeah, we have plenty of buttons
leftover from "Doomsday."

43:56.759 --> 43:59.887
Okay. Enough about me.
How was your day?

44:00.720 --> 44:03.099
We just rode around,
looked at all the main sets.

44:03.473 --> 44:04.849
Just to get the mood.

44:04.933 --> 44:06.769
I can get a vibe
of what's goin' on.

44:06.853 --> 44:09.104
- Okay, did you like it?
- Not really, no.

44:09.688 --> 44:13.358
You start tomorrow. That doesn't
really give them much time to fix things.

44:13.442 --> 44:15.443
Why is why I have to fix
the most important things.

44:15.528 --> 44:17.571
René, cheap ass.
I mean, not cheap.

44:18.281 --> 44:20.283
In the art world,
they call it a minimalist.

44:20.657 --> 44:23.201
He's a minimalist.
Not me. I like big shit.

44:23.785 --> 44:25.412
- I know.
- It's frustrating.

44:25.912 --> 44:29.125
There's this scene where this bomb
is supposed to go off in this nightclub.

44:29.208 --> 44:31.836
He wanna shoot it in a dump.
You don't shoot that in no dump.

44:31.919 --> 44:35.047
You go to Moulin Rouge,
or Folies Bergere, or somethin' big.

44:37.091 --> 44:39.426
Fuck that little shit.
You know what I'm sayin'?

44:39.510 --> 44:41.679
Herman, this is a TV show,
not a movie.

44:42.512 --> 44:46.141
- They don't have the budget.
- I know. But at the end of the day.

44:46.224 --> 44:48.477
I'm just trying to do
my best with what I know.

44:48.561 --> 44:50.812
Hollywood, blockbusters.
I grew up on 'em.

44:51.230 --> 44:54.192
- Didn"t mean to judge.
- I know I'm not a Coen Brothers.

44:55.359 --> 44:57.152
Them motherfuckers are geniuses.

44:57.236 --> 44:58.695
- No...
- Yeah.

44:58.778 --> 45:01.197
I hate when you do that.
Don't be self-deprecating.

45:01.281 --> 45:04.243
You're going to make...
great movies one day.

45:04.326 --> 45:06.787
- If movies are still being made.
- No, they will.

45:07.495 --> 45:09.164
- I got somethin' for you.
- What?

45:09.248 --> 45:10.791
- I got a surprise.
- What?

45:10.875 --> 45:12.376
Yeah... Don't move.

45:12.877 --> 45:15.129
- Are we celebrating something?
- One second.

45:19.217 --> 45:20.550
You're crazy.

45:35.649 --> 45:36.984
Yes.

45:39.695 --> 45:41.072
Baby...

45:41.739 --> 45:43.448
- Pick a hand.
- Left hand.

45:43.531 --> 45:44.991
Both, come on!

45:48.579 --> 45:50.539
It's a surprise.
Open it, it don't bite.

45:57.713 --> 45:59.714
- Herman.
- What, you don't like it?

45:59.799 --> 46:00.967
It's so beautiful.

46:02.217 --> 46:04.512
It's an apology for takin'
a hack job in Paris.

46:05.137 --> 46:08.014
- I never said it was a hack job.
- You kinda said it was a hack job.

46:08.098 --> 46:09.892
Okay, fine, I said
it was a hack job.

46:10.642 --> 46:12.019
- Wanna put it on?
- Yes.

46:12.102 --> 46:17.108
Let's do it.
This latch can be tricky.

46:19.110 --> 46:20.736
I mean, French latches.

46:24.490 --> 46:25.574
Voila.

46:33.039 --> 46:35.750
- It's gorgeous. Damn!
- I don't wanna break it.

46:36.294 --> 46:37.836
Here, let me help
you take it off.

46:41.965 --> 46:47.595
- It's so pretty.
- Mamacita!

46:50.640 --> 46:52.934
Yeah, what's up?
Shit.

46:53.728 --> 46:54.894
Goddamn!

46:56.604 --> 46:59.023
